The Speaker, Imo House of Assembly, Kennedy Ibeh says the match between Pharaohs of Egypt and the Super Eagles is the best performance by the Eagles in recent years. The speaker said this in a statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary Mr Ifeanyi Onyekachi on Wednesday in Owerri. The speaker was reacting to the Eagles 1-0 victory against the Pharaohs of Egypt at the ongoing 2021 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) in Cameroon. The game saw Nigeria dominate from the onset, leaving no space for a reply by the Egyptians.   Elephants lose first-choice ‘keeper to doping ban     Sierra Leone holds Algeria in Group E opener     Salah brutally slammed on social media   - Advertisement - “Technically, tactically, physically, mentally and whatever positive you can think of, Eguavoen’s led Super Eagles, I feel, dominated the game and this is the best Eagles performance in recent years. “At this rate, we can be extremely optimistic my people that Nigerian team is on the path to victory. “Congratulations Eagles, amazing performance lets continue to build on this momentum,” Ibeh said. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Nigeria will face Sudan for the second group D game on Saturday before meeting Guinea Bissau on Jan. 19. (NAN)